RBI Monetary Policy Impact on Nifty 50

Project Overview
This project analyzes the impact of RBI monetary policy decisions on the Nifty 50 index. 
It introduces a key idea: Market reaction depends on both expectations and actual policy.

Objectives
- Study Nifty 50 reaction to repo rate changes
- Compare expected vs surprise policies
- Analyze lag effects (0, 7, 15, 30 days)
- Identify pre-policy market behavior

Key Concept
Traditional Model:
Inflation → RBI Action → Market Reaction

Proposed Model:
Inflation → Expectation → RBI Decision → Market Reaction

Data Sources
- Nifty 50: Investing.com
- RBI Policy Data: RBI Database
- CPI Data: MOSPI

Methodology
- Event-based analysis
- Lag analysis
- Expected vs Surprise classification

Conclusion
- Markets react before RBI decisions
- Expected policies cause small movements
- Surprise policies cause high volatility
- Lag effects reveal deeper insights
